The first term in (1) is calculated by extracting characteristics from every informative read pair, where the specific characteristic modeled depends on the class of the read. Each read pair is assigned to one or more classes. If a read pair belongs to multiple classes (e.g. a read pair can be both spanning and flanking), it appears once in each class for its contribution to both likelihood classes. The read pair term is computed as follows:(2)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
